{
  "text": "Nanostructures can support strains of up to ≈ 10% without relaxation, providing great opportunities to engineer properties in ways that are not available in bulk materials [CITATION_1] . A variety of techniques exist for measuring deformation with nanometer-scale resolution, including X-ray ptychography [CITATION_2] or coherent diffraction [CITATION_3] , though at present the highest spatial resolution is achieved in the transmission electron microscope (TEM). TEM strain measurements have been accomplished by dark-field holography [CITATION_4] , atomic resolution imaging [CITATION_5] , and converged-beam techniques [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "135943536",
    "[CITATION_2]": "23125712",
    "[CITATION_3]": "10069768",
